71
00:03:10,419 --> 00:03:12,330
First, what is this 6th Schedule?

72
00:03:12,330 --> 00:03:13,905
This is the part of the Constitution

73
00:03:13,905 --> 00:03:18,390
that protects the tribal population in the country.

74
00:03:18,390 --> 00:03:20,180
According to this, in tribal areas,

75
00:03:20,180 --> 00:03:22,972
to promote democracy, the tribal people

76
00:03:22,972 --> 00:03:25,208
can form their own Autonomous District Councils

77
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:27,786
and Autonomous Regional Councils.

78
00:03:27,786 --> 00:03:29,836
Also known as ADCs and ARCs.

79
00:03:29,836 --> 00:03:31,783
They are basically elected bodies

80
00:03:31,783 --> 00:03:35,022
that have the power to administer tribal areas.

81
00:03:35,022 --> 00:03:36,358
So that on a local level, the tribal people

82
00:03:36,358 --> 00:03:42,128
make their rules about their land,
forest, and socio-cultural customs.

83
00:03:42,128 --> 00:03:46,249
So that people from outside
cannot exploit their land and resources.

84
00:03:46,249 --> 00:03:48,776
Today, this 6th Schedule is applicable

85
00:03:48,776 --> 00:03:53,085
in the tribal areas of Assam,
Meghalaya, Tripura, and Mizoram.

86
00:03:53,085 --> 00:03:55,565
Now you might think,
since there are no forests in Ladakh,

87
00:03:55,565 --> 00:03:57,736
